The paper proposes a novel method based on recurrent neural networks for missing value imputation in time series data. This method can handle multiple correlated missing values in time series and generalizes to time series with nonlinear dynamics underlying. The paper also evaluates the proposed model on three real-world datasets, including an air quality dataset, a health-care data, and a localization data for human activity. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
